text.section:
Highway user revenues distributed to Baltimore City and Kent County may be used only to pay or finance:
Costs incurred in the construction, reconstruction, or maintenance of its highways and streets;
Costs incurred by its police department for carrying out traffic functions and enforcing the traffic laws;
Costs incurred in its other highway related activities for:
Lighting the highways;
Stormwater drainage of the highways; and
Street cleaning, but not including the cost of collection of garbage, trash, and refuse;
The payment of its debt service on bonds or other evidences of obligation for:
The construction, reconstruction, or maintenance of its highways and streets; and
Any other of its highway activities, including lighting the highways and providing stormwater drainage;
The cost of transportation facilities, as defined in § 3-101 of this article;
As to Kent County:
The cost of maintaining county owned boat landings; and
Costs incurred in providing traffic crossing guards; or
As to Baltimore City, through fiscal year 2010, students' costs of discounted Maryland Transit Administration fares for eligible public school students in Baltimore City.
